---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { atlas } from '../../utils/atlas';
const stats = atlas().stats();
---
<Base title="API">
  <p class="kicker">API</p>
  <h1>Atlas API</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    The atlas is published as static JSON for analyst tooling.
    Read-only; canonical source remains the <code>atlas/</code> YAML tree
    in the repo.
  </p>

  <h2>Endpoints</h2>

  <dl class="endpoints">
    <dt><a href="/api/atlas.json"><code>GET /api/atlas.json</code></a></dt>
    <dd>
      The complete atlas as one JSON document. Includes
      <code>counts</code>, <code>nation_states</code>, <code>services</code>,
      <code>doctrines</code> (with nested pillars and programs),
      <code>actors</code> (with external_refs and aliases),
      <code>events</code> (with attributions, doctrine_links, targets,
      sources), <code>sources</code>, <code>timeline_markers</code>,
      <code>sectors</code>. <code>schema_version: 0.1</code>.
    </dd>

    <dt><a href="/api/attribution-eval.json"><code>GET /api/attribution-eval.json</code></a></dt>
    <dd>
      Leave-one-out backtest results for the actor-attribution engine:
      headline hit-rate metrics (top-1, top-3, top-5, top-10, MRR),
      per-state breakdown, top confusion pairs, worst predictions,
      and Monte Carlo stability scores. See
      <a href="/research/attribution-eval">/research/attribution-eval</a>
      for the human reading. Regenerated every build.
    </dd>

    <dt><a href="/api/doctrine-eval.json"><code>GET /api/doctrine-eval.json</code></a></dt>
    <dd>
      Leave-one-out backtest results for the doctrine-prediction
      engine: multi-label hit/recall metrics (top-1, top-3, top-5,
      recall@K, mAP), per-state breakdown, confusion, worst
      predictions. See
      <a href="/research/doctrine-eval">/research/doctrine-eval</a>.
    </dd>

    <dt><a href="/api/joint-eval.json"><code>GET /api/joint-eval.json</code></a></dt>
    <dd>
      Joint (actor × doctrine) engine backtest. Pair-hit metrics over
      the 7,381-cell (actor × doctrine) space, plus confident-hit and
      worst-prediction lists. The joint engine isn't a single-metric
      winner over the marginal engines — it's the confidence and
      novelty layer over the other two. See
      <a href="/research/joint-eval">/research/joint-eval</a>.
    </dd>

    <dt><a href="/api/pillar-eval.json"><code>GET /api/pillar-eval.json</code></a></dt>
    <dd>
      Pillar-prediction engine backtest. Predicts the specific
      doctrine pillar (MIC2025/semis vs MIC2025/aerospace, not just
      MIC2025). 129-pillar candidate space. Roughly the same accuracy
      as the doctrine engine at twice the analytic resolution. See
      <a href="/research/pillar-eval">/research/pillar-eval</a>.
    </dd>

    <dt><a href="/api/temporal-eval.json"><code>GET /api/temporal-eval.json</code></a></dt>
    <dd>
      <strong>Temporal-holdout backtest for all four engines.</strong>
      Train on events ≤ 2023-12-31, score everything after cold —
      no per-event retraining, no information leakage. The honest
      forward-prediction test. Includes per-year and per-state
      breakdowns. See <a href="/research/temporal-eval">/research/temporal-eval</a>.
    </dd>

    <dt><a href="/rss.xml"><code>GET /rss.xml</code></a></dt>
    <dd>
      RSS 2.0 feed of the 50 most recent events. Country flag, doctrine /
      attribution counts in each item's description.
    </dd>

    <dt><a href="/sitemap-index.xml"><code>GET /sitemap-index.xml</code></a></dt>
    <dd>
      Sitemap index. Points at <code>/sitemap-0.xml</code> with all
      page URLs.
    </dd>
  </dl>

  <h2>Atlas stats</h2>
  <table class="stats">
    <tbody>
      <tr><th>nation_states</th><td>{stats.nationStates}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>services</th><td>{stats.services}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>doctrines</th><td>{stats.doctrines}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>pillars</th><td>{stats.pillars}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>programs</th><td>{stats.programs}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>actors</th><td>{stats.actors}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>events</th><td>{stats.events}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>sources</th><td>{stats.sources}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>timeline_markers</th><td>{stats.timelineMarkers}</td></tr>
      <tr><th>sectors</th><td>{stats.sectors}</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Use</h2>
  <pre><code>{`# Python
import requests
r = requests.get("https://auspex.blackflagintel.com/api/atlas.json")
atlas = r.json()
print(atlas["counts"])
print(len(atlas["events"]))`}</code></pre>

  <pre><code>{`# JavaScript
const atlas = await fetch("https://auspex.blackflagintel.com/api/atlas.json")
  .then((r) => r.json());`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Stability and licensing</h2>
  <p>
    Schema follows <code>docs/DATA_MODEL.md</code> in the project repo.
    Breaking changes will bump <code>schema_version</code> in the
    payload. Cache TTL on the endpoint is short (5 minutes); the file
    is regenerated on every site build.
  </p>
  <p>
    AUSPEX content (the curated dataset) is © Black Flag Intelligence
    and made available for non-commercial research, journalism, and
    educational use with attribution. Contact for commercial licensing.
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .endpoints dt {
    margin: 1rem 0 0.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .endpoints dd {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ctp-subtext1);
  }
  .stats {
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  .stats th, .stats td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.25rem 1rem 0.25rem 0;
  }
  .stats th { color: var(--ctp-subtext0); font-weight: 500; }
  .stats td { color: var(--ctp-text); }
  pre { margin: 0.75rem 0 1.5rem; }
</style>
